title: Vann Knight Tuesday Night Criterium Series
Skills Camp KC
description:
Facebook Event – KC MTB Skills Clinic

When: Sunday, March 20th 8am – 2:30pm
Where: Stocksdale Park, 901 S. La Frenz Rd., Liberty, MO 64068
Come join us for a day of clinics with Roots Mountain Biking IMBA Certified Instructor, Jay Thomas. Jay will be offering two skills clinics.
Level 1 Skills Clinic will cover:
Body Positioning, Bike and Body Separation, Braking, Shifting, Front Wheel Lifts, Intro to Cornering
Level 2 Skills Clinic will cover:
Body Positioning, Cornering, Line Choice, Level Lift, Roll Down Lunge, Intro to Drops
NOTE: It is strongly recommended that you take the Level 1 clinic before advancing to the Level 2 clinic. The skills covered in Level 1 are useful to new and old riders alike.
Please visit www.rootsmountainbiking.com for more details on Jay’s skills clinics.
In addition to the skills clinics, Liv Ambassador Renee Thierry will be hosting a free bike maintenance clinic at Bike Stop in Blue Springs. This event will be Saturday evening. A meet & greet will start at 4:30 with the clinic beginning at 5:00. This maintenance clinic is free for anyone to attend. Bike Stop is located at 925 W US Hwy 40, Blue Springs, MO 64015.
Just when you thought there couldn’t be anything more to offer, we’re stepping it up with a presentation by Bell Joy Ride Ambassador, Samantha Jones. Samantha will share information about the Bell brand during the break time between the skills clinics.
Registration: link to come    Registration will be open through the Saturday evening clinic at Bike Stop or until both clinics fill up! There are only 10 spots in each clinic so sign up early.
Cost is $50 for one skills clinic or $80 for both.
Please make sure to have your bike and body in good working order prior to the session. Make sure to have your bike set up with flat pedals and wear sneakers. Helmets are required and body armor is recommended. Please bring a sack lunch, snacks and water.
Agenda:
Saturday, 5:00 – Liv Bike Maintenance Clinic at Bike Stop Blue Springs Location
All Sunday activities will be held at Stocksdale Park
Sunday, 8am – Skills clinic check-in
Sunday, 8:30am – Introduction
Sunday, 9:00-11:00am – Level 1 Skills Clinic
Sunday, 11:00am-12:30pm – Break and Bell Joy Ride Presentation
Sunday, 12:30pm-2:30pm – Level 2 Skills Clinic
notes: All participants are required to have a valid USAC Annual or One-Day license.
directions:
901 S La Frenz Rd
Liberty, Missouri 64068

title: Lost Valley Luau
description: A 10.5 mile loop with a mixture of flowing singletrack and doubletrack punctuated with rock formations and natural springs hosts the 10th annual Lost Valley Luau. While the gravel/ doubletrack sections are fairly flat, the singletrack sections serve up flowing, serpentine goodness with high speed descents and stunning views of the valley.
course: Trail surface varies from dirt to rock throughout the trail, and drains very well, except in the flats of the lower creek bottom.
directions: From the Highway 40/94 interchange: Take Highway 94 South approximately 1 mile on Right at the Mound.

title: Goldenberg Heller Wednesday Night TT Series
Extreme Electrical Racing's Broemmelsiek Challenge
description:
The Broemmelsiek Challenge is in its 6th year and the park was named for the family of Jack Broemmelsiek, who resided on the property for more than 30 years and dedicated their lives to promoting conservation activities. The park is 494 acres and features many natural recreation amenities for family fun.

The park opened in 2007 and offers more than 7 miles of multi use trails that are open to hiking, biking and equestrian. Nature preserves, picnicking pavilions, an astronomy viewing area, clean family friendly restrooms with running water are just a few features in this park.
course:
A loop of fast and flowy hardpack single track through the woodlands including some creek crossings and field sections, 
Kids race will be a separate shorter loop with a few challenges.
registration:
Online registeragtion is available with USAC
Prices are discounted until 3/24/2016
Online registration closes 4/21/2016
Onsite registration is subject to a $5 fee in addition to your race/license fees.
All registration closes 30 minutes prior to race start times.
notes:
Events are subject to weather.
Annual USAC license is required for Cat 1 and Pro only Optional for Cat 2 and Cat 3. One day only license is required for all non annual license holders.
Helmets must be worn at all times while on the bike at UFD events.
Promoter reserves the right to cancel/combine events/prize lists as necessary. 
Promoter reserves the right to adjust mileage and start times if needed.
Have Fun, Race Clean, Enjoy The Outdoors....No Whining!
directions:
From I-64 / MO DD / Winghaven exit head south on Hwy DD for 4.7 miles to Park enterance on right. Head into park and take first left up the hill to the pavilion. 
Overflow parking is down near the lake.
